## 4.4 Delivery Radius Visualization

### The Current Experience

The customer sees a map with a store marker and their delivery pin. There's no visual indicator of where the delivery boundary is — they only find out when the panel says "DELIVERY NOT AVAILABLE".

### The New Experience

A semi-transparent circle centered on the store showing the max delivery radius:

```
        ┌─────────────────────────────┐
        │      ·  ·  ·  ·  ·         │
        │    ·                ·       │
        │   ·      🔵 Store    ·      │
        │   ·                 ·       │
        │    ·    📍 Pin      ·       │
        │      ·  ·  ·  ·  ·         │
        │              ← radius circle │
        │                             │
        └─────────────────────────────┘
```

The circle uses a soft semi-transparent fill so it doesn't obscure map details, with a subtle stroke at the boundary edge.

### Implementation

#### [MODIFY] `alw-checkout-map.js`

Add circle rendering inside `initMap()`, after the store marker:

```javascript
// Delivery radius visualization
var deliveryCircle = new google.maps.Circle({
    map: map,
    center: storeLatLng,
    radius: MAX_KM * 1000,  // Convert km to meters
    fillColor: '#4285F4',
    fillOpacity: 0.06,       // Very subtle fill
    strokeColor: '#4285F4',
    strokeOpacity: 0.3,
    strokeWeight: 2,
    clickable: false,        // Don't interfere with map clicks
    zIndex: 1,               // Behind markers
});
```

That's it — 10 lines. `google.maps.Circle` handles all the projection math. The circle automatically adjusts its visual shape for map projection at different zoom levels.

### Visual Design Decisions

| Parameter | Value | Rationale |
|---|---|---|
| `fillOpacity: 0.06` | Nearly transparent | Just enough to see the boundary without hiding map details |
| `strokeOpacity: 0.3` | Subtle edge | Clearly marks the boundary without being visually heavy |
| `strokeWeight: 2` | Thin line | Visible at all zoom levels without dominating |
| `fillColor: '#4285F4'` | Google Blue | Matches the store marker color for visual consistency |
| `clickable: false` | Non-interactive | Doesn't block click-to-place-pin functionality |

### Tiered Pricing Circle Enhancement

If distance tiers are active, we could show multiple concentric circles — one per tier — with different colors to visualize the pricing zones:

```javascript
if (config.pricing_mode === 'tiered' && config.distance_tiers) {
    var colors = ['#059669', '#eab308', '#ef4444']; // green → yellow → red
    config.distance_tiers.forEach(function(tier, i) {
        new google.maps.Circle({
            map: map,
            center: storeLatLng,
            radius: tier.to * 1000,
            fillColor: colors[i % colors.length],
            fillOpacity: 0.04,
            strokeColor: colors[i % colors.length],
            strokeOpacity: 0.25,
            strokeWeight: 1,
            clickable: false,
        });
    });
}
```

This creates a beautiful, informative visualization where customers can see at a glance which pricing zone they're in.

